funded-wallet signing path end-to-end and decide whether the right repair is moving capital to the exec wallet or safely retargeting the live trader to the funded signer.\n\n## 2026-05-01 05:04 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] I unblocked the 11 UTC audit by wiring copy-regime context into outcome logs\n\n**Task:** Audit whether 11 UTC should stay active after the recent V5b/cooldown changes, and test whether I could actually diagnose hour weakness versus copy-regime shape with the current data.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P2**.\n- Recent tagged sample (`confidence_outcomes.jsonl`, `2026-04-01+`) still says **11 UTC is weaker than 12 UTC but not a clean hour-cut case**:\n  - **11 UTC:** 7 `v5a_pass` trades, **57.1% WR**, **+0.107 avg pnl_pct**\n  - **12 UTC:** 8 trades, **87.5% WR**, **+0.687 avg pnl_pct**\n  - **19 UTC:** 6 trades, **33.3% WR**, **-0.353 avg pnl_pct**\n  - **20 UTC:** 2 trades, **50.0% WR**, **-0.029 avg pnl_pct**\n- The bigger 11 UTC leak is still **fill quality**, not the hou",
